Do developers use only URL for the images and should I change the column type to URL like the Portfolio? How do they typically handle storing images?

Not usually. Developers typically do not change image columns to plain URL fields unless they have a specific reason.

The common pattern
Most apps store images in 2 parts:

the actual image file lives in storage

S3

Cloudinary

Firebase Storage

Xano file/image storage

similar object storage

the database stores a reference to that file

a URL

a file object

a path

metadata like width, height, filename

So the DB usually does not store the raw image itself.

For your case
If Xano already has:

profile_picture as image

portfolio_images as array of image

that is usually the better setup than changing them to plain text URL columns.

Why:

it is more structured

easier for uploads later

better for validation

more future-proof

Why you may be seeing URL-like behavior
Many systems return image fields to the frontend as:

a direct URL string, or

an object that contains a URL

That is normal.

So even if the field type is image, the frontend often still ends up rendering a URL in <img src="">.

Should you change profile_picture to URL?
I would say:

No, not right now.

Keep it as an image field unless:

you are never uploading through Xano

you only want to paste external image links manually

you want a very simple MVP with no file handling

If you expect real users or tailors to upload profile pictures later, image type is better.

What developers typically do
Option A: Managed image/file field
Best for many app builders and low-code backends.

user uploads image

backend stores file

DB stores reference/metadata

frontend receives usable URL

Option B: Plain URL field
Simpler, but more limited.

DB stores only a pasted image link

no upload workflow built in

depends on external hosting

can break if external URL disappears

Which is better for each field
profile_picture
Keep as image

one main image

likely uploaded by tailor

good candidate for managed file handling

portfolio_images
Keep as array of image

multiple uploaded images

very standard marketplace pattern

better than array of text URLs

Best practical advice for your app
For a tailor marketplace:

profile_picture → image

portfolio_images → array of image

only use URL/text fields for things like:

whatsapp_link

website link

Instagram link

What the frontend should do
The frontend should simply be flexible enough to handle the image field response shape, whether Xano returns:

a string URL

an object with url

an array of either

That is a frontend parsing issue, not a reason to change your schema.

Recommendation
Keep:

profile_picture as image

portfolio_images as array of image

Do not switch to URL columns just to make rendering easier.

Instead, improve the frontend so it can read Xano’s image response shape correctly.

