That error means the form is reaching Xano, but the image field format is not what the endpoint logic expects.

What the error means
Xano is complaining about:

Missing param: path
payload: {
  param: inspiration_image_upload.path
}
So somewhere in your create_booking endpoint, Xano is trying to read:

inspiration_image_upload.path

But the frontend is sending a regular uploaded file through FormData, not an object with a path property.

In plain English
Your frontend is likely doing the right browser thing:

sending a file

But your Xano endpoint logic is likely written as if inspiration_image_upload already looks like:

an image/file object

with fields like path

Those are not the same thing.

Most likely cause
Inside the Xano endpoint, one of the function-stack steps is probably referencing:

inspiration_image_upload.path

instead of just using:

inspiration_image_upload

or using the correct upload/file handling step.

What to check in Xano
Open the POST /create_booking endpoint and inspect the function stack.

Look for any step that:

adds the booking record

transforms the image input

references inspiration_image_upload.path

That is the step causing the error.

The likely fix
If your booking table field inspiration_image_upload is an image column, then when creating the record, you usually want to map:

table field inspiration_image_upload = input inspiration_image_upload

not:

table field inspiration_image_upload = inspiration_image_upload.path

Why this happens
There are usually 2 different patterns:

Pattern A: direct file/image input
The endpoint accepts an uploaded file/image directly.
Then you usually pass the input field itself into the image column.

Pattern B: object/path-based handling
The endpoint expects some processed file object and then reads a property like path.

Your current frontend is using Pattern A, but your Xano logic appears to be written like Pattern B.

What I think you should do
In Xano, update the booking creation step so the image field uses the raw input:

inspiration_image_upload

instead of:

inspiration_image_upload.path

